description.narrative: Health districts in the priority regions have the capacity and systems to implement programmes and a package of integrated quality interventions for pregnant and lactating women, newborns and children under five, especially the most disadvantaged., which contributes to Access To Justice, Child Health, Child Health (Covid), Cross-Sectoral Communication For Development, Early Childhood Development, Early Childhood Development (Covid), Harmful Practices (Fgm/C And Child Marriage), Harmful Practices (Fgm/C And Child Marriage) (Covid), Immunization, Immunization (Covid), Maternal And Newborn Health, Maternal And Newborn Health (Covid), Operations Support To Programme Delivery, Other Cross-Sectoral Programme Areas, Prevention Of Stunting And Other Forms Of Malnutrition, Prevention Of Stunting And Other Forms Of Malnutrition (Covid), Sanitation, Sanitation (Covid), Treatment And Care Of Children Living With Hiv, Treatment Of Severe Acute Malnutrition, Treatment Of Severe Acute Malnutrition (Covid), Water, Water (Covid). UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Public Engagement, Developing And Leveraging Resources And Partnerships, Evaluations, Research And Data, Fostering Innovation And Use Of New Technologies, Harnessing Power Of Business And Markets, Operational Support To Programme Delivery, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building, United Nations Working Together. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: Young girls and boys (0â€“5 years), particularly the most deprived and hard-to-reach, are immunized, well nourished, healthy, protected, registered at birth and prepared for school, including in humanitarian situations.
